  <summary date="2019-07-25T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Great Lakes Coastal Resiliency Act of 2019

This bill requires the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers to assess the resiliency of the Great Lakes coastline, with a focus on (1) areas vulnerable to rising water levels and severe weather; and (2) lake conditions that contribute to coastal erosion, sustained flooding, and damage to properties and critical infrastructure.</summary>
